<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

<p>This guideline outlines the steps to build a hybrid inventory and accounting system for our Catalyst application.</p>

<p>The system will support:</p>
<ul>
    <li>3D printing materials and products</li>
    <li>Herbs and related products</li>
    <li>Bee-related products</li>
</ul>

<p>The system uses <strong>LedgerSMB</strong> (an open-source ERP, formerly SQL-Ledger) for inventory and accounting, integrated with our <strong>Catalyst</strong> application for member stores and geolocation-based order routing.</p>

<h2 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h2>

<h3>Environment Requirements</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Perl 5.36+</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL 15+ with PostGIS</li>
    <li>Catalyst 5.901+</li>
    <li>PyCharm with Zencoder plugin</li>
</ul>

<h3>Hardware Requirements</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Server with 4GB RAM minimum</li>
    <li>20GB storage minimum</li>
    <li>Example configurations:
        <ul>
            <li>AWS EC2 t3.medium</li>
            <li>DigitalOcean droplet with equivalent specs</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Dependencies</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Required Perl modules:
        <ul>
            <li>DBIx::Class</li>
            <li>Catalyst::Controller::REST</li>
            <li>Catalyst::Plugin::Authentication</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Database: PostgreSQL with PostGIS extension</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="step_by_step">Step-by-Step Implementation</h2>

<h3 id="step1">Step 1: Set Up LedgerSMB</h3>

<p>Install and configure LedgerSMB to handle inventory and accounting for all sites.</p>

<h4>Installation Steps</h4>
<ol>
    <li>Download LedgerSMB (latest stable, e.g., 1.11.x) from <a href="https://ledgersmb.org">ledgersmb.org</a>.</li>
    <li>Install required system packages:
        <pre><code class="language-bash">sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y postgresql postgresql-contrib
</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>Clone the repository and install dependencies:
        <pre><code class="language-bash">git clone https://github.com/ledgersmb/LedgerSMB.git
cd LedgerSMB
cpanm --installdeps .
</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>Set up PostgreSQL database:
        <pre><code class="language-bash">sudo -u postgres createuser -s ledgersmb
sudo -u postgres createdb ledgersmb
</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>Run the setup script:
        <pre><code class="language-bash">perl setup.pl
</code></pre>
    </li>
</ol>

<h3 id="step2">Step 2: Configure Inventory and Accounting</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Access the web interface at: <code>http://your-server:5000</code></li>
    <li>Complete the initial setup wizard</li>
    <li>Create a new company (e.g., "Catalyst Inventory")</li>
    <li>Configure chart of accounts</li>
    <li>Set up inventory categories:
        <ul>
            <li>3D Printing Materials</li>
            <li>Herbs</li>
            <li>Bee Products</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h3 id="zencoder_prompt">Zencoder Prompt</h3>

<div class="card bg-light mb-3">
    <div class="card-header">Zencoder Prompt for Database Initialization</div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <pre><code>Generate a Perl script to initialize LedgerSMB's PostgreSQL database with sample data for:
- 3D printing (filament, PLA, 1kg, $20)
- Herbs (basil, 100g, $5)
- Bee products (honey, 500g, $10)

Include assemblies for:
- 3D-printed model (2 parts)
- Herb blend (basil + oregano)</code></pre>
    </div>
</div>

